==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idolatry
<hw>I*dol"a*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Idolatries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>idol⟦acir⟧trie</ets>, LL. <ets>idolatria</ets>, L.
<ets>idololatria</ets>, Fr. Gr. <?/; <?/ idol + <?/ service.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The worship of idols, images, or anything which is not
God; the worship of false gods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His eye surveyed the dark <qex>idolatries</qex>⟦br⟧
Of alienated Judah.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Excessive attachment or veneration for anything;
respect or love which borders on adoration.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idolish</ent>⟦br⟧
